<br>
<blockquote><br>
I like griefers. Anything to spice up the normal day to day grind of DAOC. This game needs a bit more excitement.<br>
</blockquote><br>
<br>
So I assume you're going to be playing on the PvP server? Good for you--be sure to write. For the rest of us, we're not looking for any exploiters to add "excitement" to the game.<br>
<br>
<blockquote><br>
If the developers/coders present a product that still seems to be in a "beta" mode, don't we have the right to try anything we find?<br>
</blockquote><br>
<br>
You don't have that right. Re-read your end user license again, it will point you to the Rules of Conduct, which you agree to abide by every time you play the game:<br>
<br>
<blockquote><br>
PLAYER MAY NOT USE THE DAoC SERVICES TO: <br>
<br>
12. Abuse or exploit bugs, undocumented features, design errors or problems in the game collectively referred to as Problems. Player acknowledges and agrees to report all problems, errors or bugs in the game to Mythic as soon as they are found as their continued use can damage the enjoyment of the game for all its players.  Mythic will do everything within their power to fix these types of issues in a timely manner, and will give all customers the benefit of the doubt when dealing with these problems.<br>
</blockquote><br>
<br>
Read that one more time... Mythic will give you the benefit of the doubt. You should be glad, in EQ they just ban you even if it was an accident.<br>
<br>
You don't have the rights to "try anything we find". You have one important right:<br>
<br>
<blockquote><br>
13. Termination<br>
<br>
* Either you or Mythic may terminate your Account, for any reason, without further obligation to the other.<br>
</blockquote><br>
<br>
You wanna talk the talk? Walk the walk and hit the cancel account button if you want Mythic to know how unhappy you are with the "'beta' mode" the game is in. Even Sanya agrees that the only way to get the big-wigs attention. Me, Mythic gets my money... cheaper than a night out dancing and I can kill the guys that pester me.<br>
